:begin[en]
GT{Spongilla fluviatilis. Fresh-water sponge. Trituration of the dried sponge gathered in autumn.}
:rubric=Clinical.
S{Breast, cancer of. Bruises. Bubo. Catarrh. Chilblains. Coryza. Eyes, pains in. Glands, affections of. Hay-fever. Haemorrhoids. Heart, affections of. Indurations. Ophthalmia. Palpitation. Rheumatism. Scrofula. Syphilis. Tibia, pain in. Whooping-cough.}
:rubric=Characteristics.
S{R[Bad] is the Russian name for the river sponge, which is a popular Russian remedy. Among the peculiar symptoms and indications are: Headache with aching in backs of eyeballs, 2 p.m. to 7 p.m.; B[<] motion. Severe headache in vertex B[>] night, returning severely after breakfast. Headache with inflamed eyes. Pains in eyeballs extending to head. (J. A. Biegler cured a case with the following symptoms: A lady had for months off and on a severe pain in r. eyeball, which extended to forehead over this eye, then to temple; always B[<] in afternoon.) Scalp sore; dry; itching; scurf; tetters. Soreness is one of the key-notes of the remedy; general soreness of integuments and muscles; as if beaten; very sensitive. Profuse coryza, coming from nostril with a gush. L. cheek and malar bone sore to touch. Lancinating pains in stomach; liver; below scapulae; urethra; chest. Buboes. Chancres suppressed by cautery. Infantile syphilis. Carcinoma of breast. There is a cough which causes sneezing, profuse coryza. Occasional severe fit of coughing ejecting viscid mucus flying out of mouth; caused by tickling in larynx as if a particle of sugar was dissolving in throat; B[>] in warm room. Tremulous vibrative palpitation B[<] lying r. side. Palpitation after pleasurable emotions. Soreness of anterior muscles of legs; toes bend while walking as if extensors were paralysed. It has lessened a hard cellular swelling of both legs. Sharp stinging back of r. heel, B[<] least pressure. Chronic rheumatism, B[<] by cold, especially in cold air. B[<] Stormy weather. B[>] In warm room; B[<] afternoon. B[<] Pressure and touch: there is general soreness, even to touch of clothes. Sore as if beaten. Headache B[>] at night, after sleep.}
:rubric=Relations.
:rubric2=Compare
S{R[Spong]; R[Seneg] (cough 2[caused] by sneezing, opposite of Bad.); R[Grin] (respiration ceases on falling asleep); Spo. (cough with much sneezing); R[Kali-c] (phlegm flies from mouth); R[Calc-s] (indurations); R[Carb-an] (indurations, buboes); R[Cist] (scrofula); R[Clem], R[Hep], R[Iod], R[Kali-i], R[Lach], R[Merc], R[Merc-i-f], R[Nit-ac], R[Sil], R[Sulph].} 
:rubric2=Followed well by:
S{R[Lach]} 
:rubric2=Complementary to:
S{R[Sulph], R[Iod], R[Merc.]}
:head=SYMPTOMS.
:rubric=1. Mind.
S{After pleasurable emotions, palpitation.} S{Mind generally clear, active in spite of headache.}
:rubric=2. Head.
S{Headache from 2 p.m. to 7 p.m., with slight aching pains in the posterior portion of both eyeballs, and in the temples.} S{During the day more or less headache, with pain in the eyeballs (worse l.); more from 1 p.m. to 7 p.m.} S{Frontal headache during the forenoon, worse in the temples, and extending into the posterior portion of the l. eyeball; B[<] by moving the eye.} S{Pain in the temples and eyeballs; from eyeballs to temples.} S{A very severe headache on top of the head; remains the same in all positions; better at night after sleeping, and better in the morning; returning violently after breakfast; lasting several days.} S{Headache with inflamed eyes.} S{Headache B[<] on moving eyes.} S{Excess of dandruff, or dry, tetter-like appearance of the scalp, with slight itching; hair dry.} S{Scalp sore to touch, with tetter-like eruption on forehead.}
:rubric=3. Eyes.
S{Bluish-purple margin of the eyelids, and blue under the eyes.} S{Scrofulous inflammation of the eyes, with hardening of the Meibomian glands.} S{Severe pain from eyeballs (B[<] l.) into temple; B[<] turning eyes.} S{Intermittent neuralgia of r. eyeball, extending to temple, B[<] afternoon.} S{Headache extending into the eyeballs.} S{L. eyeball quite sore, even upon closing it tightly.} S{Twitching of l. eyelid.}
:rubric=4. Ears.
S{Slight shocks heard in the ear, as of very distant artillery; afternoons.}
:rubric=5. Nose.
S{Profuse coryza, mostly from the l. nostril; comes with a gush; worse in afternoon and evening; with sneezing.} S{Coryza and cough.} S{Itching of l. ala nasi.}
:rubric=6. Face.
S{On forehead, tetter-like eruption.} S{Pale, ashy, or leaden colour of face.} S{Stiffness in the maxillary joints.} S{L. cheek and malar bone sore to touch.}
:rubric=8. Mouth.
S{Mouth and breath hot and feverish, with thirst for large quantities of water at a time.} S{Mouth and tongue feel scalded.}
:rubric=9. Throat.
S{Hawks up, in morning, masses of gluey bloody mucus from throat, which is inflamed and sore, B[<] swallowing, solids.} S{Tonsils red, inflamed, B[<] swallowing solids.}
:rubric=11. Stomach.
S{Pressure in epigastrium, nausea, and rumbling.} S{Lancinating in pit of stomach 8 a.m.; extends to vertebrae, r. scapula, at times to r. side, resulting there in pleuritic pain.}
:rubric=12. Abdomen.
S{Lancinating pain with a bounding movement in region of liver.} S{Indurated inguinal glands.} S{Syphilitic buboes.}
:rubric=13. Stool and Anus.
S{Catarrh of the bowels.} S{Constipation.} S{Haemorrhoids.}
:rubric=14. Urinary Organs.
S{Severe, sharp, lancinating pain in or near orifice of urethra.} S{Urine high-coloured; and reddish.}
:rubric=15. Male Sexual Organs.
S{Chancres, after cautery, elevated discoloured cicatrices, rhagades.} S{Syphilis of infants, whole convolutes of hard glandular swellings, buboes.}
:rubric=16. Female Sexual Organs.
S{Carcinoma mammae.} S{Metrorrhagia B[<] night, with feeling of enlargement of head.}
:rubric=17. Respiratory Organs.
S{Breath hot and feverish.} S{Occasional severe paroxysms of spasmodic cough, ejecting viscid mucus from the bronchial tubes, which at times comes flying forcibly out of the mouth, B[<] afternoon and evening, caused by tickling in the larynx, as if sugar was dissolving, B[>] in warm room.} S{Cough 2[=] sneezing; profuse coryza.} S{Pain in upper part of r. chest.} S{Pleuritic pain, B[<] on motion or on full inspiration; with soreness.} S{Severe, sharp, lancinating pain in r. supra-clavicular region.} S{Stitches in sides, esp. r.} S{While lying on r. side in bed, and at moment of becoming unconscious by sleep, severe oppressive suffocative attacks from suspended respiration, causing a quick effort to prevent suffocation by changing position.} S{Typhoid pneumonia.}
:rubric=19. Heart.
S{Severe vibrating, tremulous palpitation of the heart, even while sitting or lying, quiet, upon any sudden elating or other emotion of mind.} S{Lying on r. side, heart is heard and felt to pulsate from chest up to neck.}
:rubric=20. Neck and Back.
S{Very stiff neck.} S{Soreness and lameness, with stitches in nape of neck, B[<] by bending the head back and forth.} S{Scrofulous swelling of the glands of the l. side of the face, throat, and neck; nearly as large as a hen's egg; some hard, some suppurating.} S{Severe lancinating pains and stitches in the posterior r. side, below the scapula, much B[<] by throwing the shoulders back and chest forward, or any contortions of the body; pain extorting at times a mean or shriek.}
:rubric=22. Upper Limbs.
S{Palms of hands hot and dry.}
:rubric=23. Lower Limbs.
S{Several hard, small lumps along the shin-bone.} S{Hard cellular swelling of the legs.} S{Anterior muscles of r. leg sore, as if beaten.} S{At night violent lancinating pains in the limbs.} S{Hard swellings of both legs lessened.} S{Hurts of horses' hoofs.} S{Bad ulcers of horses' feet.} S{Toes bend while walking as if extensors paralysed.} S{Checked foot-sweat.}
:rubric=24. Generalities.
S{General soreness of the muscles and integuments of the whole body; flesh sore to touch, even of the clothes; sore as if beaten.}
:rubric=25. Skin.
S{Skin sore to touch.} S{Raised and discoloured scars.} S{Rhagades.} S{Brown and blue spots after concussions.} S{Externally applied causes checked eruptions to reappear.} S{Tetters on scalp and forehead; itching on scalp.}
:rubric=26. Sleep.
S{Restless at night; must frequently change position, body feels so sore.} S{Awake 3-4 a.m. with frightful dreams and severe cramping pains in metatarsal bones of both feet.} S{B[>] After sleep (head).}
:end
